Duduzile Ramela spoke to Marlin Joseph, who is part of the Community Policing Forum. #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - A search is on for the bodies of two children after drowning on Sunday. Two teenagers aged 13 and 16 drowned in a river in Kliptown, Soweto. Marlin Joseph, who is part of the Community Policing Forum (CPF) says the teens drowned after trying to rescue one of their friends. The community as well as authorities rallied together to search for the bodies.